				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Position Title:</strong> CIRES Administrative Assistant (TEMP)<strong><br />
</strong><strong>Reports To: </strong>Contract Compliance Coordinator<br />
<strong>Team:</strong> Immigration &amp; Refugee – Miami Office<br />
<strong>Salary: </strong>$15 hourly-20 hours a week</p>
<p>Church World Service (CWS) is a not-for-profit organization working to eradicate hunger and poverty and to promote peace and justice around the world. CWS does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, age, disability or veteran status in employment or in the provision of services.</p>
<p><strong>Apply:</strong></p>
<p>Please visit the link below to apply directly online to this position.</p>
<p><a href="http://cws.applicantstack.com/x/apply/a2h9xbo8e5bp">http://cws.applicantstack.com/x/apply/a2h9xbo8e5bp</a></p>
<p><strong><u>Primary Purpose</u></strong><strong>:<br />
</strong>The primary purpose of the position is to monitor data entered into the RSDS Database by the multi-agency (CWS, St. Thomas Human Rights Institute, AIJ and Catholic Charities) Legal Programs. Incumbent is responsible for assisting the Contract Compliance Coordinator in conducting multi-agency compliance, monitoring and the compiling and submission of all narrative reports to the funding source.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Essential Duties</span>:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Responsible for maintaining documentation and records of all sub-contracts for the Legal Programs in Miami Dade, Broward and Palm Beach Counties.</li>
<li>Provide Assistance to the Contract Compliance Coordinator in compiling statistical data for the sub-contracted service providers to ensure the integrity of the reports generated from the provider’s databases is accurate and documented.</li>
<li>Assist the Contract Compliance Coordinator with on-site monitoring reviews of contracted service providers to ascertain level of compliance.</li>
<li>Maintain current program review tools, various state/federal/local guidelines, program directives and policies, provide technical and systems support to staff and service providers.</li>
<li>Assist the Contract Compliance Coordinator with the scheduling of monitoring visits for multi-agency legal programs. This includes preparing appropriate compliance report checklist of visiting agencies to be monitored.</li>
<li>Collaborates with the various legal providers and Program Coordinators in the design and implementation of new programs and grants.</li>
<li>In collaboration with the Contract Compliance Coordinator, ensures contract compliance by conducting periodic monitoring and evaluations of the multi-agency legal providers.<strong> </strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Qualifications:  </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Strong organizational, diplomatic and priority setting skills.</li>
<li>Strategic thinker, with proven ability to handle multiple tasks, handles pressure and meets deadlines.</li>
<li>In depth knowledge of refugee and immigrant-related programs and protocols</li>
<li>Good understanding of the State of Florida funded programs.</li>
<li>Energetic individual with clear and effective written and oral communication skills.</li>
<li>Ability to work well, both independently, and within a team.</li>
<li>Ability to work under pressure and deadlines.</li>
<li>Self-starter.<strong> </strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Education:  </strong>Associates Degree in related field or equivalent experience.</p>
<p><strong>Experience:<br />
</strong>Two years professional contract management or program evaluation experience. Knowledge of Access/Excel and MS Office Suite required. Knowledge of Oracle preferred.<strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Other Skills:<br />
</strong>Computer literacy in word processing, spreadsheet, database and Web-based applications. Strong verbal and written communication skills in English required.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cwsglobal.org/1388-cires-administrative-assistant-temp-miami-fl/">CIRES Administrative Assistant (TEMP)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cwsglobal.org">CWS</a>.</p>
