		<title>Why become a sustaining partner?</title>
		<link>https://cwsglobal.org/sustaining-partner-story/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2018 14:50:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[CWS]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://cwsglobal.org/?p=5228</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>A note from some faithful friends We donate to CWS because it has a long-standing reputation as a thoughtful, strategic, credible, and effective organization. We appreciate their approach to developing sustainable solutions to some of the world’s most challenging problems while remaining ready to respond to disasters. Like many people, our lives are incredibly busy. [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cwsglobal.org/sustaining-partner-story/">Why become a sustaining partner?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cwsglobal.org">CWS</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A note from some faithful friends</p>
<img class="wp-image-5237 size-large alignright" src="https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="525" srcset="https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game-300x225.jpg 300w, https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game-768x576.jpg 768w, https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game-700x525.jpg 700w, https://cwsglobal.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Moran-Kracht-Family-soccer-game.jpg 1254w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" />
<p>We donate to CWS because it has a long-standing reputation as a thoughtful, strategic, credible, and effective organization. We appreciate their approach to developing sustainable solutions to some of the world’s most challenging problems while remaining ready to respond to disasters.</p>
<p>Like many people, our lives are incredibly busy. We both work full time and we have an active 5-year old daughter. Our best intentions to donate were getting lost in the day-to-day shuffle. We found ourselves feeling frustrated when we didn’t follow through with our planned donations, so several years ago we set up recurring monthly gifts. In addition to the convenience, we also appreciate the benefit of giving in monthly amounts that can be built into our family’s budget.</p>
<p>Poverty and hunger are ongoing, and our efforts to support solutions should be as well. Also, when a crisis happens, CWS responds immediately. Regular gifts from donors like us ensure that there are adequate funds to provide support when needed.</p>
<p>We hope others will join us as CWS Sustaining Partners because ongoing donations from monthly donors help CWS make thoughtful, strategic plans for the future.</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br />
The Moran-Kracht Family</p>
<p><a href="/sustaining-partners">Become a Sustaining Partner today!</a></p>
